Also don't start with writing the big novel, start smaller. Short fictions, writing excercises etc. until you have some command of your style. Ideas aren't the problem, ideas are a dime a dozen when you start to look for them. You may get ideas from shorter 4000 word pieces that can turn into something 100000 words long. Only way to be a good writer, is read a lot, write a lot. <br>
