<br>
Try and develop your own world, first. I'm a builder/pseudo-admin on the up and coming MUD, Against the Grain, and literally have just about creative control over it all, and I'm not the owner (lady friend of mine). As in, I created the Gods, I created the races, I created the continents, mapped out the cities and everything. That's what you really need to do. Just create a world, and things will begin to flow. <br>
<br>
Or maybe I took the writer's block too metaphorically. If you're literally having trouble starting it off and you've already created main characters, try opening up with a memory. I love first-person novels, as you really get to know what's going on. Introductions aren't that big, though. Heh, I recall a book that opened up with something like(excuse the language), &quot;No shit, there I was...&quot; Cursed, yes, but it was effective (The character was in the middle of a battle, confused, scared, and really wanted to get out of there). Anyway, if you post more specifics I can probably help more. <p>Vall Shadowstrife <BR>
